class Solution {
    public int leastOpsExpressTarget(int x, int target) {
        if (x == target) return 0;
        if (x > target) return 1;

        int ops = 0;
        while (x < target) {
            if ((target - x) % x == 0) {
                ops += (target - x) / x;
                return ops;
            }
            target += x;
            ops++;
        }
        return ops + 1;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(target/x))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iteratively increases the target by x until it is divisible by x. At each step, it checks if the remaining difference between target and x is divisible by x. If it is, the function returns the number of operations. Otherwise, it increments the target by x and the number of operations by 1. This greedy approach ensures the minimum number of operations.

